pair A = moo(1/1997), B = moo(2/1997);

draw(A--B);
draw(rightanglemark(A, (0,0), B, 10));
[/asy]

Let $v$ and $w$ be two of these roots.  Then $|v| = |w| = 1,$ so by the Triangle Inequality,
\[|v + w| \le |v| + |w| = 2.\]Equality occurs when $v$ and $w$ are diametrically opposite.

Furthermore,
\[|v + w|^2 = (v + w)(\overline{v + w}) = (v + w)(\overline{v} + \overline{w}) = |v|^2 + |w|^2 + v \overline{w} + \overline{v} w = 2 + 2 \operatorname{Re} (v \overline{w}).\]Since $v$ and $w$ are roots of unity, $|v \overline{w}| = 1,$ so
\[2 \operatorname{Re} (v \overline{w}) = 2 \cos \theta,\]where $\theta$ is the angle between $v$ and $w.$

[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);

pair moo (real t) {
