dot((1,0));

pair A = moo(1/1997), B = moo(2/1997);

draw(A--B);
draw(rightanglemark(A, (0,0), B, 10));

label("$\theta$", (0.2,0.1));
[/asy]

Thus,
\[|v + w|^2 = 2 + 2 \cos \theta.\]We want to find the probability that
\[\sqrt{2 + \sqrt{3}} \le |v + w|.\]This is equivalent to
\[\sqrt{2 + \sqrt{3}} \le \sqrt{2 + 2 \cos \theta},\]or $\sqrt{3} \le 2 \cos \theta.$  This means $\cos \theta \ge \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2},$ so $\theta \le 30^\circ.$

