draw(A--B);
draw(rightanglemark(A, (0,0), B, 10));

label("$\theta$", (0.2,0.1));
[/asy]

Since the roots are evenly spaced, the probability that $\theta \le 30^\circ$ is equal to the ratio of the arc length corresponding to an angle of $30^\circ$ to the circumference of the unit circle:
\[\frac{30^\circ}{360^\circ} = \boxed{\frac{1}{12}}.\]

